<a name="ih69-fannin-exit"></a>
<div class="problem-heading">Southbound IH-69 Exit Ramp to Fannin</div>
<div class="textblock">
    <div class="problem-solution">Problem</div>
    <ul>
        <li>The exit to Fannin is eliminated and replaced with an exit to Almeda Road. This will force vehicles through six traffic signals to reach Fannin using a route with two turns. </li>

        <li>Proceeding to the west from the Almeda exit will be difficult and inconvenient since east-west streets are not equipped to handle through-traffic</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="problem-solution">Potential Solution</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Add an exit to Wheeler and Fannin at the Metro train station. This can be done with no further acquistion of private property. The exit goes underneath Fannin and then rises up to the surface. Connecting to Wheeler is optional depending on vertical alignment.</li>
        <li>The loop ramp to Fannin will replace the functionality of the exiting exit to Fannin, providing excellent access into this area where people are actually going, and also providing much improved access to points to the west, including Montrose.</li>
    </ul>

</div>

